<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     5. KEY THINGS TO KNOW (Tabs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="cd-tabs">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Key Things to Know</h2>
    <div class="cd-tabs__wrap">
      <div class="cd-tabs__nav">
        <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="1">Native Performance<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="2">App Store Approval<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="3">iOS Security & Privacy<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="4">Push Notifications & Engagement<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="5">TestFlight & QA<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
      </div>
      <div class="cd-tabs__content">
        <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="1">
          <p>Native iOS apps built with Swift deliver the fastest, most responsive experience possible on Apple hardware. Unlike web or hybrid approaches, native code talks directly to the device's APIs, unlocking Metal graphics, CoreML on-device intelligence, and precise haptic feedback that users expect from premium iOS apps.</p><p>The Demski Group optimizes every layer — from memory management to rendering pipelines — ensuring your app remains fluid at 60 or 120 fps on ProMotion displays and handles intensive workloads without draining the battery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="2">
          <p>Navigating App Store review can be challenging, with Apple's guidelines evolving regularly. Our team stays current with every policy change — from privacy requirements and in-app purchase rules to content moderation standards — so your submission sails through review without costly delays.</p><p>We also optimize your App Store listing with keyword-rich metadata, compelling screenshots, and preview videos, giving your app the best chance of ranking and converting visitors into downloads from day one.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="3">
          <p>Apple has built privacy into the core of iOS, and users expect apps to honor that commitment. The Demski Group implements App Tracking Transparency, on-device data processing, and end-to-end encryption as standard practices, not afterthoughts.</p><p>We also ensure your app is fully compliant with App Store privacy nutrition labels, correctly declaring data usage so users can make informed choices and regulators find nothing to flag during review.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="4">
          <p>iOS push notifications, when used thoughtfully, are one of the highest-ROI engagement tools available. We implement APNs (Apple Push Notification service) with rich media, interactive actions, and personalized payloads that bring users back to your app at exactly the right moment.</p><p>Combined with in-app messaging, widgets, and App Clips, our engagement architecture keeps your audience connected to your product across the entire Apple ecosystem — iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch, and beyond.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="5">
          <p>Before a single user sees your app, we run it through a rigorous quality assurance pipeline on real devices spanning the full range of active iOS versions and screen sizes. Automated UI tests, unit tests, and performance benchmarks catch regressions early in the cycle.</p><p>TestFlight beta distribution lets your stakeholders validate every release before it goes to production, ensuring that what ships is exactly what was approved — polished, reliable, and ready for the App Store spotlight.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

