<section class="cd-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="true">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          What is the difference between Swift and Objective-C?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" style="display:block;">Swift is Apple's modern programming language — concise, safe, and fast. Objective-C is the legacy language with a mature ecosystem of libraries. We typically recommend Swift for new projects and can maintain or migrate Objective-C codebases when needed.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          How long does it take to build an iOS app?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">A simple app can be completed in 6–10 weeks; a complex enterprise solution may take 4–6 months. We provide a detailed timeline during the proposal phase after understanding your specific requirements.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Do you handle App Store submission?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. We manage the entire submission process — certificates, provisioning profiles, metadata, screenshots, and the review interface — so you don't have to navigate Apple's ecosystem alone.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Will my app work on older iPhones?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">We set a minimum iOS version that balances access to modern APIs with the widest device coverage. Typically we target the last 2–3 major iOS versions, covering over 95% of active devices.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Can you update an existing iOS app?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Absolutely. Whether you need a design refresh, a feature addition, or a full SwiftUI migration, we can take over any existing codebase and bring it up to current standards.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

